Constructor Detail

ElementInstance

public ElementInstance(java.lang.String id,
                       ElementType elemType,
                       boolean makeDefault)
Creates an element instance. If a default ElementInstance is defined in elemType and we say to use it, it is used as a prototype to create this instance. TODO: creare anche le prop ereditate, per avere i default di quelle che non sono valorizzate

Parameters:
id - id of the instance
elemType - the ElementType of this instance
makeDefault - a boolean to tell the constructor to build the default element instance or not. Useful if you are loading from file and don't want to make elements that are not described in the file itself
